Description: Shoulder sherd with handle root (in toto thirteen joining and non-joining fragments) of large East Greek Grey Ware pottery oenochoe; light grey fabric with numerous mica and limestone inclusions; dark slip (almost completely worn); exterior: decoration in added relief and incision consisting of large palmette on 'Aeolic' capital below handle attachment; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Uncertain place of manufacture, though the inscription is in full Ionic alphabet
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 327)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 670, no. 288)
Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (A630)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.070)
